morning sun ( chinese : &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ; pinyin : &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; de &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ) is a 2003 documentary film by &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; hinton about the cultural revolution in china . the film uses archival and propaganda footage from the era as well as interviews with red guard participants and victims to explore the events and effects of the cultural revolution . in the united states , the film garnered largely positive reviews . it won the american historical association john e. o'connor film award in 2004 and was nominated or a finalist in regards to a handful of other awards and film festivals .